title: Two missionaries released in Haiti after group kidnapping
description: Two missionaries kidnapped in Haiti over a month ago have been released, according to a statement by the US-based Christian Aid Ministries. CNN has not been able to independently confirm their release.

title: Missing tennis star appears on video call with Olympic and Chinese officials
Missing tennis star appears on video call with Olympic and Chinese officials
description: International Olympic Committee (IOC) president Thomas Bach held a video phone call with three-time Olympian Peng Shuai, the Olympics governing body announced on Sunday.

title: Residents evacuated from Italian island Vulcano over carbon dioxide levels
description: Most of the 250 permanent residents of a volcanic Italian island have been told to evacuate after levels of carbon dioxide in the air spiked dangerously, causing respiratory problems to people and their pets.

title: Justin Bieber called on to cancel Saudi Arabia concert by slain journalist's fiancée
description: The fiancée of murdered journalist Jamal Khashoggi wrote an open letter published by the Washington Post calling for Justin Bieber to cancel his upcoming concert in Saudi Arabia.

title: Tiger Woods posts first video taking practice swings since car accident in February
description: Golfing legend Tiger Woods posted a short video of himself taking a practice shot out on a golf course on Sunday.

title: Adele wants you to listen to her album in order, and Spotify agrees
description: When it comes to her art, Adele has a certain way she likes things to be done. The singer believes the tracks on an album should be listened to in their order of arrangement -- and now she's got streaming giant Spotify onside.

title: Sudan's military reinstates prime minister ousted after last month's coup
description: Sudan's military chief and the prime minister he overthrew last month have reached a deal for the reinstatement of the premier and the release of jailed political detainees, mediators said Sunday.

title: Violent clashes erupt during anti-lockdown demonstrations in Europe
description: Protests in European countries against new Covid-19 restrictions turned violent over the weekend as cases continue to rise in the continent.

title: Lewis Hamilton wins Qatar Grand Prix
description: Lewis Hamilton put in a faultless drive to win Sunday's inaugural Qatar Grand Prix and cut Max Verstappen's championship lead to just eight points.

title: There's nothing more frightening in America today than an angry White man
description: The Brute. The Buck. And, of course, the Thug.

title: 'SNL' has Judge Jeanine go over the Kyle Rittenhouse verdict and a chat with Donald Trump
description: There was a lot of news to cover from this week, and "Saturday Night Live" had its Judge Jeanine take it all on.

title: Arsenal boss explains fiery clash with Jurgen Klopp during defeat to Liverpool
description: Arsenal boss Mikel Arteta played down his furious touchline row with Liverpool head coach Jurgen Klopp during the Gunners' 4-0 defeat at Anfield on Saturday.

title: Manchester United manager out after club suffered humiliating Premier League defeat
description: Manchester United have confirmed the departure of manager Ole Gunnar Solskjaer, one day after the club suffered a humiliating 4-1 Premier League defeat at Watford.

title: The victims of the Belarus border crisis were obvious. For Poland's government, it was a useful distraction
description: It was clear who the losers were in the dispute between Poland and Belarus. The thousands of migrants who became stranded on the border in freezing conditions had their dreams of a new future in Europe dashed, and some are now being repatriated to their home countries. But for Poland's government, the crisis helped to divert attention from a series of uncomfortable issues.

title: Meet the 70-year-old who is believed to be the oldest woman to climb Yosemite's El Capitan
description: Dierdre Wolownick dreamed of watching the sunset from the top of Yosemite National Park's famous El Capitan rock formation in California.

title: She died from a snakebite. But the real killer was her husband
description: Uthra's mother found her daughter lying motionless in bed at the family home, her left arm dotted with blood.
